|ORmen= Bob Beamon 8.90 m (1968) |WRwomen= Galina Chistyakova 7.52 m (1988)
|ORwomen= Jackie Joyner 7.40 m (1988) }} The 'long jump' (formerly commonly
called the "broad jump") is a track and field event in which athletes combine
speed, strength, and agility in an attempt to leap as far as possible from a
take off point. This event has been an Olympic medal event since the first
modern Olympics in 1896 (a medal event for women since 1948) and has a history
in the Ancient Olympic Games.
